    "body": "@iamdefinitelyahuman I have something basic up, but 1) it's not quite working yet, and 2) I'm still thinking about what should be in charge of loading the env file. It seems like a responsibility of `main.py`. An earlier implementation I had done was loading it in the config container, but I don't think the config container should be in charge of something stateful like loading an env file.\r\n\r\nThat said, if we do want to support POSIX-style variable interpolation, we'd probably want access in the ConfigContainer level so that we only have to parse once.\r\n\r\nThoughts? ",
